    },
    "body": "Problem: Subclassing GemmSm100 for specialized GEMM variants (e.g., MoE grouped GEMM) requires overriding the MMA K-tile depth. Currently mma_inst_tile_k = 4 is hardcoded inside _setup_attributes, which feeds into downstream SMEM layout, pipeline stage, and cluster shape calculations. \r\n\r\nIn the MoE kernel, each mainloop iteration has additional overhead that doesn't exist in the standard GEMM.\r\n\r\nThere's no way to change it without either:\r\n- Copying the entire _setup_attributes (~150 lines) into the subclass\r\n- Monkey-patching after _setup_attributes, which breaks because downstream calculations already used the old value\r\n\r\nSolution: Extract the hardcoded 4 into a one-line virtual method _get_mma_inst_tile_k() that subclasses can override.\r\n\r\nUse case: Our MoE GEMM kernel (MoeGemmSm100(GemmSm100)) overrides this to return 8 for BF16 (128-element K-tile to amortize per-expert prefix-sum overhead) and 4 for blockscaled MXFP8.\r\n\r\nImpact: +8 lines, zero behavioral change, purely additive extensibility point. All existing tests pass unmodified.",
